s of immersive fieldwork and more than a hundred interviews, he describes a country in transition, one struggling to negotiate the fluid boundaries of culture, tradition, and modernity. Harkness shows how Qataris reaffirm—and challenge—traditions in many areas of everyday life, from dating and marriage, to clothing and humor, to gender and sports. A cultural study of citizenship in modern Qatar, this book offers an illuminating portrait that cannot be found elsewhere.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Mrz 2024) 0aForeign workerszQatar. 0aSex rolezQatar. 0aWomenzQatarxSocial conditionsy21st century. 70(DE-588)4001307-80(DE-627)1063975910(DE-576)20884225XaAlltag2gnd 70(DE-588)4015602-30(DE-627)1063359870(DE-576)208912614aEthik2gnd 70(DE-588)4020588-50(DE-627)1063175200(DE-576)208933956aGesellschaft2gnd 70(DE-588)4060560-70(DE-627)1061391180(DE-576)209135743aTradition2gnd 70(DE-588)4113450-30(DE-627)1058293900(DE-576)209476583aEntwicklung2gnd 70(DE-588)4120755-50(DE-627)10577426X0(DE-576)20953768XaModernisierung2gnd 70(DE-588)4121849-80(DE-627)1057666150(DE-576)209546689aVerhaltensmuster2gnd 70(DE-588)4135971-90(DE-627)1056610660(DE-576)209665238aWertordnung2gnd 70(DE-588)4138354-00(DE-627)10415151X0(DE-576)209685336aLebensstil2gnd 70(DE-588)4227561-10(DE-627)1049628520(DE-576)210323450aSoziokultureller Wandel2gnd 70(DE-588)4323955-90(DE-627)1284369050(DE-576)211249572aTraditionale Kultur2gnd 7aHISTORY / Middle East / Arabian Peninsula.2bisacsh  a2022.  aArabian Gulf.  aArranged marriage.  aBranding.  aCitizenship.  aClothing.  aComedy.  aConsanguineous marriage.  aConsanguinity.  aCulture.  aExpatriates.  aFIFA.  aGlobal South.  aHijab.  aHistory.  aIslam.  aLabor.  aMarriage.  aMicropractices.  aMiddle East.  aModern